name: Deneb Algedi

Destination of USS Enterprise in Encounter at Farpoint.

Constellation: Cygnus

Distance: 3,230 light years

Star Type: A2 Ia

Mass: 19 sol

Radius: 203 sol

Luminosity: 196,000 sol

Surface Temperature: 8,525K

Rotational Velocity: 20 km/s

Age: Uncertain

name: Rigil Kentaurus
commentary: Alpha Centauri A, along with Alpha Centauri B and Proxima Centauri (Alpha Centauri C) form the Alpha Centauri system. Alpha Centauri is considered a visual binary star, meaning it appears as one star with a visual magnitude of -0.28 when viewed with the naked eye, making it the third brightest star behind Sirius (-1.46) and Canopus (-0.72). Alpha Centauri A, on its own would appear to be the night sky’s fourth brightest star, with an apparent magnitude of 0.02.
